</div><span class="hide-when-compact"><i> (<small><a href="/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal" title="Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a></small>)</i></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>Islamic eschatology</b> (<a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" dir="rtl">عِلْم آخر الزمان في الإسلام</span>, <span title="Arabic-language romanization"><i lang="ar-Latn">‘ilm ākhir az-zamān fī al-islām</i></span>) is a field of study in <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islam</a> concerning future events that would happen in the <a href="/wiki/Eschatology" title="Eschatology">end times</a>. It is primarily based on sources from the <a href="/wiki/Quran" title="Quran">Quran</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sunnah" title="Sunnah">Sunnah</a>. Aspects from this field of study include the <a href="/wiki/Signs_of_the_coming_of_Judgement_Day" title="Signs of the coming of Judgement Day">signs</a> of the final age, the destruction of the universe and <a href="/wiki/Last_Judgment" title="Last Judgment">Judgement Day</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-EoQ1_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EoQ1-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-EoQ2_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EoQ2-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-:3_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:3-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
